The paper deals with fair division of resources, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC). The Fisher market and Trading Post mechanisms are both models of economic exchange, which fall under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The analysis of the performance of these mechanisms involves studying the approximation of objective functions, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implementation of these mechanisms, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
